Class HumanPlayer

java.lang.Object
demoreee.Character
demoreee.HumanPlayer
public class HumanPlayer
extends Character
The HumanPlayer class implements mechanisms such as user inputted controls or the level reset.

  • Constructor Details

    • HumanPlayer

      public HumanPlayer​(java.lang.String name, javafx.scene.layout.Pane p_gameRoot, java.util.ArrayList<javafx.scene.image.ImageView> levelPlayers, java.util.ArrayList<javafx.scene.image.ImageView> levelPlatforms, java.util.ArrayList<javafx.scene.Node> levelPickups, java.util.ArrayList<javafx.scene.Node> levelHazards, int startX, int startY, int width, int height, javafx.scene.input.KeyCode controlsLeft, javafx.scene.input.KeyCode controlsRight, javafx.scene.input.KeyCode controlsJump)
      A function that creates the humanPlayer. It follows specific movement rules. It can only move left, right or jump. It is affected by gravity.
      Parameters:
      name - - The name of the player.
      p_gameRoot - - The gameplay root.
      levelPlayers - - the players who are playing the game.
      levelPlatforms - - The array containing level architecture.
      levelPickups - - The array containing level pickups.
      levelHazards - - The array containing level hazards, that are fatal for the player if encountered.
      startX - - The start x coordinate of the entity.
      startY - - The start y coordinate of the entity.
      width - - The widith of the entity.
      height - - The height of the entity.
      controlsLeft - - The control which moves the player to the left.
      controlsRight - - The control which moves the player to the right.
      controlsJump - - The control which makes the player perform a jump action.
